  "prompt": "What is your favorite T-shirt wash?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don't have personal preferences or feelings, but I can offer some recommendations for washing T-shirts! \n\n1. **Cold Water:** Washing T-shirts in cold water helps preserve the fabric and color.\n   \n2. **Gentle Cycle:** Use a gentle cycle to reduce wear and tear on the fabric.\n\n3. **Mild Detergent:** Choose a mild detergent to avoid harsh chemicals that could damage the material.\n\n4. **Avoid Bleach:** Bleach can weaken the fibers and damage colors.\n\n5. **Air Dry:** Drying T-shirts in the dryer on high heat can cause shrinkage and fading. It's better to air dry them or use a low heat setting.\n\nIf you have specific fabric requirements or washing instructions provided by the manufacturer, it's best to follow those guidelines for optimal care.",
